  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Landscape in Merapi and Merbabu Vulcano Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local community, producers, civil society, public sector institutions, companies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Majority of farmers in Merapi and Merbabu surrounding areas are reliant on subsistence agriculture. As they are operating at small-scale so they face challenges of lack of skill and knowledge, access to technologies, low productivity, profitability and lack of access to the wider market. The project interventions are focused on community based sustainable landscape practices, along with enhanced knowledge of farmers about sustainable agriculture, climate smart practices and broader access to market. Public and private sector stakeholders would be engaged through multi-stakeholder platform. The knowledge and application of climate smart agriculture practices would build farmers resilience to climate change and contribute for enhancing livelihood and food security.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of project is to build knowledge and capacities of farmers about landscape management practices, climate smart agriculture and broader access to markets with engagement of public and private sector stakeholders. The knowledge and application of climate smart agriculture practices would build farmers resilience to climate change and contribute for enhancing their livelihood and food security.</narrative>
  </description>
